The paper discusses the application of deep learning algorithms in the field of m-Health, specifically for analyzing sleep patterns. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper addresses the challenges of limited computational resources in wearable devices, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of neural engineering (cs.NE), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and software engineering (cs.SD).
